      "type": "feat",
      "img": "icons/svg/aura.svg",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>The toad swallows a Medium or smaller target it is grappling. While swallowed, o alvo isn't Agarrado but has the Cego and Impedido conditions, and it has Total Cover against attacks and other effects outside the toad. In addition, o alvo takes 10 (3d6) dano de ácido at the end of each of the toad's turns. The toad can have only one target swallowed at a time, and it can't use Mordida while it has a swallowed target. If the toad dies, a swallowed creature is no longer Impedido and can escape from the corpse using 1,5 m of movement, exiting with a condição Caído.</p>",
          "chat": ""
        },
